block main
  // #PAGE HEADER
  // PAGE HEADER
  .page-header
    .row
      .col-md-4
        .media
          .media-left.media-middle
            i.ion-stats-bars.fa-2x
          .media-body
            .display-6 Chart UI
            .small.text-muted 
              | Chart UI Design
  
  // #CHART
  .container-fluid
    .panel-wrapper

      .panel
        .panel-heading
          h6.panel-title 
            | Peity
            a.small(href="http://benpickles.github.io/peity/" target="_blank") official website
        .panel-body
          .row
            .col-md-6
              table.table
                thead
                  tr
                    th OrderDate
                    th Region
                    th Rep
                    th Units
                tbody
                  tr
                    td 1/6/2014
                    td East
                    td Jones
                    td: span(data-plugin="peityPie" data-peity='{ "fill": ["#4183D7", "#f1f1f1"], "radius": 10 }') 1/6
                  tr
                    td 1/6/2014
                    td East
                    td Jones
                    td: span(data-plugin='peityBar' data-peity='{ "fill": ["#4183D7"], "width": 50 }') 0,-3,-6,-4,-5,-4,-7,-3,-5,-2
                  tr
                    td 1/6/2014
                    td East
                    td Jones
                    td: span(data-plugin='peityBar' data-peity='{ "fill": ["#4183D7"], "width": 50 }') 0,-3,-6,5,2,3,-7,-3,-5,-2
                  tr
                    td 1/6/2014
                    td East
                    td Jones
                    td: span(data-plugin="peityDonut" data-peity='{ "fill": ["#4183D7", "#f1f1f1"], "radius": 10 }') 4/6
                  tr
                    td 1/6/2014
                    td East
                    td Jones
                    td: span(data-plugin='peityLine' data-peity='{ "fill": ["#4183D7"], "width": 50 }')  22,14,12,43,32

            .col-md-6
              p Peity (sounds like deity) is a simple jQuery plugin that converts an element's content into a simple mini pie  donut  line  or bar chart  and is compatible with any browser that supports: Chrome, Firefox, IE9+, Opera, Safari.
              
              h4.demo-sub-title.m-t-3 Theme usage
              pre(data-src="assets/markups/chart-peity.html")

      .panel
        .panel-heading
          h6.panel-title 
            | Easy pie chart
            a.small(href="https://rendro.github.io/easy-pie-chart/" target="_blank") official website
        .panel-body
          .row
            .col-md-6
              .row
                .col-sm-6
                  .easypie.center-block
                    span(data-plugin="easyPieChart" data-percent="73") 73 %
                .col-sm-6
                  .easypie.center-block
                    span(data-plugin="easyPieChart" data-percent="22") 22 %

            .col-md-6
              p Easy pie chart is a jQuery plugin that uses the canvas element to render simple pie charts for single values. These charts are highly customizable, very easy to implement, scale to the resolution of the display of the client to provide sharp charts even on retina displays, and use requestAnimationFrame for smooth animations on modern devices.
              
              h4.demo-sub-title.m-t-3 Theme usage
              pre(data-src="assets/markups/chart-easy-pie.html")
      
      .panel
        .panel-heading
          h6.panel-title 
            | Chart js
            a.small(href="http://www.chartjs.org/" target="_blank") official website
        .panel-body
          .row
            .col-md-6
              #demo-bar-chart-legend.legend.legend-inline.pull-xs-right
              canvas#demo-bar-chart

              .m-t-3
                #demo-line-chart-legend.legend.legend-inline.pull-xs-right
                canvas#demo-line-chart

              .m-t-3
                #demo-doughnut-chart-legend.legend.legend-inline.pull-xs-right
                canvas#demo-doughnut-chart
            .col-md-6
              p: strong Six chart types
              p Visualize your data in 6 different ways. Each of them animated, with a load of customisation options and interactivity extensions. get more infomation, please check 
                a(href="http://www.chartjs.org/docs/" target="_blank") chart js official documentation
              
              h4.demo-sub-title.m-t-3 Theme usage
              p Make sure change your chart legend template markup.
              pre(data-src="assets/markups/chart-theme.js")
                  



block js
  script(src="assets/scripts/demo/bar-chart.js")
  script(src="assets/scripts/demo/line-chart.js")
  script(src="assets/scripts/demo/doughnut-chart.js")












